<h1>ANSWERS</h1>
			<div id = "post-ans" class = "post">
				<p>If you <strong><em>add two spaces</em></strong> after a word and enter a line break/return, the markdown engine will insert a line break automagically. This disables the rewrapping that is designed into the editing system.</p>

<p>So
if 
you
enter
lines
like
this, they wrap.</p>

<p>But<br>
if<br>
you<br>
double<br>
space, then they don't wrap.</p>

<p>(click the <a href="https://apple.meta.stackexchange.com/posts/1623/revisions">history link</a> to see my source)</p>

<p>This is documented in the <a href="https://apple.stackexchange.com/editing-help">advanced editing help</a> section, which you can get to from any editing frame by clicking the blue circle around the question mark to the right of the edit toolbar.</p>

